        "old_string": "# Django pre_validate Signal Implementation\n\n## Signal System Pattern\n- Model signals are defined in `django/db/models/signals.py` as instances of `ModelSignal`\n- `ModelSignal` is a subclass of `Signal` that supports lazy model specification\n- All model lifecycle signals use `use_caching=True`\n- Signals are dispatched using `.send()` with `sender=` (the model class) and keyword args for context\n\n## Existing Model Lifecycle Signals\n- `pre_init` / `post_init` - Model instantiation\n- `pre_save` / `post_save` - Model saving\n- `pre_delete` / `post_delete` - Model deletion\n- `m2m_changed` - Many-to-many relationship changes\n\n## Validation Flow\n- Model validation happens in `full_clean()` method (line 1690 in base.py)\n- Calls `clean_fields()`, then `clean()`, then `validate_unique()`, then `validate_constraints()`\n- Signal should be dispatched at the **start of `full_clean()`** before any validation\n\n## Implementation Details\n- Add `pre_validate = ModelSignal(use_caching=True)` to signals.py\n- Import in base.py from signals module\n- Dispatch in full_clean() with sender=origin, instance=self, and relevant params",
        "new_string": "# Django pre_validate Signal Implementation - COMPLETED \u2713\n\n## Implementation Summary\nSuccessfully added `pre_validate` signal to Django's model signals module following the exact pattern of existing lifecycle signals.\n\n## Changes Made\n\n### 1. django/db/models/signals.py (Line 51)\nAdded: `pre_validate = ModelSignal(use_caching=True)`\n\n### 2. django/db/models/base.py\n- Line 53: Added `pre_validate,` to imports from `django.db.models.signals`\n- Lines 1697-1703: Dispatched signal at start of `full_clean()` with parameters:\n  - sender=self.__class__\n  - instance=self\n  - exclude=exclude\n  - validate_unique=validate_unique\n  - validate_constraints=validate_constraints\n\n## Signal Lifecycle\nFires before: clean_fields() \u2192 clean() \u2192 validate_unique() \u2192 validate_constraints()\n\n## Verification\n\u2713 Valid Python syntax\n\u2713 Follows exact pattern of pre_save/pre_delete/etc.\n\u2713 Signal definition: ModelSignal with use_caching=True\n\u2713 Dispatched at correct point (start of full_clean)\n\u2713 Includes validation context parameters",
